===================== ZERO SETUP REQUIRED! =====================

📦 WHAT'S INCLUDED:
✅ Docker configuration - Everything runs in containers
✅ MySQL database - Pre-configured
✅ phpMyAdmin - Database manager (http://localhost:8080)
✅ All Python dependencies - Pre-installed
✅ Test suite - Ready to run

🚀 HOW TO RUN (WINDOWS):

Step 1: Install Docker Desktop
   • Download from: https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/
   • Install and restart computer
   • Start Docker Desktop (wait for it to show "Running")

Step 2: Install VcXsrv (for GUI)
   • Download from: https://sourceforge.net/projects/vcxsrv/
   • Install with default settings
   • Run XLaunch from Start Menu
   • Select: Multiple windows → Display 0 → No client → ✓ Disable access control

Step 3: Run SecurePixel
   • Open PowerShell in this folder
   • Type: docker-compose up
   • Wait 2-3 minutes for first launch
   • GUI will appear automatically!

🔑 DEFAULT LOGIN:
   Username: admin
   Password: admin123

📊 PHPMYADMIN:
   URL: http://localhost:8080
   User: stegouser
   Pass: stegopassword

🛑 TO STOP:
   Press Ctrl+C in PowerShell, then type: docker-compose down

❓ TROUBLESHOOTING:
   • If GUI doesn't appear: Make sure VcXsrv is running
   • If ports are busy: Run "docker-compose -p securepixel up"
   • To reset everything: "docker-compose down -v"

🎉 THAT'S IT! NO PYTHON, NO MYSQL, NO DEPENDENCIES TO INSTALL!


## 🔧 Troubleshooting

### GUI doesn't appear?
- Make sure VcXsrv is running
- Windows Firewall might block it - allow VcXsrv
- Run `run.bat` again

### Docker errors?
- Run PowerShell as Administrator
- Run: `wsl --update`
- Restart Docker Desktop

### Database connection issues?
- Wait 30 seconds for MySQL to fully start
- Check if ports 3307 and 8080 are free
- Run: `docker-compose logs mysql`

